                <head>Immigration</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>John D. Imboden writes the editors of the Richmond Dispatch to explain his
                    scheme to promote immigration in the state of Virginia. He proposes encouraging
                    Europeans who can pay their own way and have the money to purchase land to
                    settle in the state. He does not wish to attract "mere laborers" like those who
                    settle in New York.</summary>
